WEBVTT

00:01.734 --> 00:03.566
Here are my car keys.

00:03.870 --> 00:06.600
Ashley has a birthday party
to go to on Saturday afternoon.

00:06.673 --> 00:09.506
And Carlton may use the car
to go to glee club practice.

00:09.576 --> 00:10.907
And Master William?

00:10.977 --> 00:14.378
He's not allowed to use the car again
until August of 1992.

00:15.415 --> 00:17.007
Very well, madam.

00:17.083 --> 00:18.675
Everybody, I'm going.

00:18.752 --> 00:22.188
Excuse me, Mother,
but I am very, very offended.

00:22.956 --> 00:26.050
What is it this time, Hilary?
I've started recycling.

00:27.794 --> 00:31.093
That's not it. Instead of making
Geoffrey work on the weekend...

00:31.164 --> 00:33.564
you should leave the running
of this household to me.

00:33.633 --> 00:35.362
I am 21 years old.

00:39.272 --> 00:42.469
I'm sorry, baby. I didn't think
you'd want to run the household.

00:42.542 --> 00:44.169
I've got to learn sometime.

00:44.244 --> 00:48.203
After all, in a couple of years, I'm going
to have my own family and my own butler.

00:48.281 --> 00:50.249
I hope it's no one I know.

00:52.385 --> 00:54.444
- Ready to go, sweetheart?
- All set.

00:54.521 --> 00:57.319
If you had to pick a weekend to go away,
you picked a good one.

00:57.390 --> 01:00.257
I'll be at the office working
most of the time anyway.

01:00.326 --> 01:03.489
If you have a lot of work to do,
why don't you just do it here?

01:11.604 --> 01:12.730
That's why.

01:14.307 --> 01:16.867
How y'all doing?
I just got my hair cut. Kind of fly, huh?

01:16.943 --> 01:19.434
I don't understand why
you get your hair cut like that.

01:19.512 --> 01:22.003
All the brothers in Philly
play their hair like this...

01:22.082 --> 01:23.913
hair on top, none on the sides.

01:23.983 --> 01:26.952
But, I guess y'all got kind of
a reverse thing going on here.

01:31.324 --> 01:34.157
- Will, I'm leaving.
- You're leaving?

01:34.227 --> 01:37.390
Finally. I always thought
you could do better. Good luck.

01:37.630 --> 01:40.531
Will, I'm going to Berkeley
to give my lecture.

01:40.600 --> 01:43.592
- You are? When you coming back?
- Tomorrow night. While I'm gone...

01:43.670 --> 01:46.537
I want you to do everything
your Uncle Philip says.

01:51.177 --> 01:53.702
Aunt Viv, wait. Don't leave me here.

01:53.780 --> 01:57.580
Don't leave me here with him!
He's going to eat me. Don't leave me here.

